               <head>Sihr-i halal</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Siḥr-i ḥalāl by Ahlī Shīrāzī, Muḥammad ibn Yūsuf, 1454-1535 or 1536</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85100084" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Or_15663-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_36817419">Ahlī Shīrāzī, Muḥammad ibn Yūsuf, 1454-1535 or 1536</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="person_36817419" type="supplied">اهلي شيرازي، محمد بن يوسف</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_7025">Siḥr-i ḥalāl</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_7025">سحر حلال</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>A mas̲navī poem on the love-story of Prince Jam and Princess Gul, with a preface in prose, by Muḥammad Ahlī Shīrāzī (d. 942/1535-6). </p>
                        <p>This poem has several remarkable artistic features: it has two different rhymes and scans in two metres; and each bayt contains a tajnīs.</p>
                        <p>Other contents: owner’s inscription with title and price, f. 1v.</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>
						</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
